In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 30, 2012, as Gold Star Mother's and Family's Day. He pays tribute to the men and women in uniform who have sacrificed their lives to defend their country. The President honors the families who have lost loved ones in service, acknowledging the grief and burden they carry. He calls on all Americans to support and serve these families as they have served the nation. The President encourages government officials and the American people to display the flag and hold appropriate ceremonies to show sympathy and respect for Gold Star Mothers and Families.